commit.message:
Issue/188 (#198)

* quick fix for ignoring a usual location for venv.

* decode using iso-8859-1 and if this fails, raise the MWSError with the original xml attached to .response

* comment in the code to show WHY we are returning this. The developer using this can then take a good look at the XML to find out why it has failed to decode and report back to us any issues.

* duplicate the tests and inject a known problem char (\x94) to make sure the decoding works.

These tests are currently not passing on my computer due to hashable object issues with pytest, but were quite happy on Github actions.

Committing and pushing to see what result we get in the pipeline.

* code format with black.

* Test re-writes, should work now.

* Black formatting fix

Co-authored-by: Galen Rice <galen.s.rice@gmail.com>

Adding GitHub Action CI workflow (#191)

* Add GitHub CI actions

Bring things in-house, so to speak. If this works well, can remove dependency on TravisCI for these actions.

* Remove flake8 linting

* Remove py3.4 testing

* Change manual codecov command to action

Noted here: https://github.com/marketplace/actions/codecov

* Change back from f-string

Breaks on Python<3.6

* Setup.py Blacked

* Remove support for <3.5

* Remove the workflow dispatch trigger

* Multiple OSs in the test matrix

* Massive README update

* Add requests to requirements file

* Ignore .venv folder

* Change testing note (not Travis)

* Change around requirements
Install pytest and pytest-cov in the testing workflow, not from requirements
Simplify requirements to those required for the project to run
Move development requirements to requirements-dev.txt
